Introduction

In our project, we analyze if air quality in New York City increased during last years. For these purposes, we use New York City air quality surveillance data (https://catalog.data.gov/dataset/air-quality). We investigate dynamics of 18 indexes of air quality. Some of them are considered separately for adults and children. Our dataset consists of 18,025 observations. One observation is value for some index for some period for some geo place. Respectively, values for all indexes that are presented on plots are averaged by geo places. In general, our data covers period 2005-2022 but for some indexes it is narrower.

ggplot(averaged_data_1, aes(x = Period, y = Value, group = 1)) +
  geom_point() +
  geom_line() +
  labs(title = "Average annual vehicle miles traveled",
       x = "Time period",
       y = "Million miles per square mile")

Average annual vehicle miles traveled grew from 67.17757 million miles per square mile in 2005 to 79.96636 million miles per square mile in 2019. It tells us about potential decrease of air quality.

Conclusion

Almost all indicators of air quality in New York city were improved during the analyzed period. Some deterioration is observed in miles traveled by cars. However, increase in fuel efficiency of vehicles allowed to avoid growth of emissions. Some increase is also observed in average Ozone (O3). However, in general, air quality grew.
